# ResumeWing — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in only the keys you actually need.
# NEVER commit your `.env` file — it is in `.gitignore`.
# All keys stay on YOUR machine; nothing is sent to any ResumeWing server.
#
# Six of the twelve job boards work with NO key (The Muse, RemoteOK, Remotive,
# Arbeitnow, Jobicy, Himalayas) so you can ship a working install with an
# empty `.env`. Add keys below to unlock more sources / higher volume.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── TIER 1: PRIMARY SOURCES (best quality, US-focused, real-time data) ────────

# JSearch via RapidAPI — real-time Google for Jobs.
# Covers LinkedIn, Indeed, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter, and 50+ boards in one call.
# Free tier: 200 requests/month.
# Get key: rapidapi.com → search "JSearch" by OpenWeb Ninja → Subscribe Free
#          → Your Apps → Default App → Authorization → copy X-RapidAPI-Key
JSEARCH_API_KEY=

# Adzuna — stable free API, millions of US listings.
# Free tier: 250 requests/day. Get both keys at developer.adzuna.com
ADZUNA_APP_ID=
ADZUNA_API_KEY=


# ── TIER 2: SUPPLEMENTAL SOURCES (free, federal jobs, niche aggregators) ──────

# USAJobs — official US federal government job board.
# Always-valid links; great for DC/VA/MD and near federal agencies.
# Free registration (instant): developer.usajobs.gov/apirequest
# USAJOBS_USER_AGENT MUST be your email address — required by the API.
USAJOBS_API_KEY=
USAJOBS_USER_AGENT=

# Findwork — tech & developer roles, clean API, free key.
# Get key: findwork.dev → Register → copy API Token
FINDWORK_API_KEY=

# Jooble — large global job aggregator, free key.
# Request via: jooble.org/api/about
JOOBLE_API_KEY=

# Careerjet — massive US aggregator with strong onsite + remote coverage.
# Free publisher key: careerjet.com/partners/register/as-publisher
CAREERJET_API_KEY=


# ── LOCAL LLM (Ollama) — optional, defaults are sensible ──────────────────────
# Only set these if you've moved Ollama to a non-standard host/port or want
# a different model. The app falls back to deterministic templates if Ollama
# isn't reachable.
# OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2:3b
# OLLAMA_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=20
# OLLAMA_MAX_PARALLEL=4


# ── DAILY DIGEST EMAIL — optional, runs via Windows Task Scheduler / cron ─────
# When configured, digest_email.py runs once a day, searches the keywords
# below across every job board you've enabled above, scores results against
# your latest resume, and emails the top N matches to DIGEST_EMAIL_TO.
#
# Auth uses SMTP with a Gmail App Password — no OAuth, no Google Cloud project.
# Steps:
#   1. Enable 2-Factor Auth on the sender Gmail account (the DIGEST_SMTP_USER
#      account). Without 2FA, App Passwords are not available.
#   2. Visit https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#   3. App = "Mail", Device = "Other (ResumeWing)" — click Generate.
#   4. Paste the 16-character string (spaces optional) as DIGEST_SMTP_PASSWORD.
#   5. Register the daily task (one line in PowerShell or cmd):
#        schtasks /Create /TN ResumeWingDigest ^
#                 /TR "<full path>\job-app-automation\run_digest.bat" ^
#                 /SC DAILY /ST 08:00 /F
#
# Leave DIGEST_EMAIL_TO blank to disable the feature entirely.
DIGEST_EMAIL_TO=
DIGEST_SMTP_USER=
DIGEST_SMTP_PASSWORD=
DIGEST_KEYWORDS=Software Engineer,Backend Engineer,Full Stack Engineer

# DIGEST_LOCATION accepts a single value OR a comma-separated list. Each value
# triggers its own search cycle; results are merged + deduped across cycles.
# Examples:
#   DIGEST_LOCATION=United States              ← onsite/hybrid US + remote-only boards
#   DIGEST_LOCATION=United States,Remote       ← also queries every board with "Remote"
#   DIGEST_LOCATION=Boston,New York,Remote     ← multi-city + remote
#
# Quota tip: JSearch is 200 requests/month free. The script makes roughly
#   (keywords × locations) JSearch calls per day. With 5 keywords × 2 locations
#   that's ~300/month — over the limit. Keep keywords × locations ≤ ~6 to stay
#   under, or run the digest 5 days/week instead of 7.
DIGEST_LOCATION=United States,Remote

# Optional tuning — defaults are sensible.
# DIGEST_TOP_N=5               # how many ranked matches to email each run
# DIGEST_NUM_PER_BOARD=10      # per-board fetch cap (keep low to save quota)
# DIGEST_MAX_AGE_DAYS=7        # ignore postings older than N days
# DIGEST_SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# DIGEST_SMTP_PORT=587
# DIGEST_DASHBOARD_URL=http://localhost:3000
